$ modinfo i915
filename:       /lib/modules/6.18.39-0-lts/kernel/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915.ko
author:         Intel Corporation
author:         Tungsten Graphics, Inc.
description:    Intel Graphics
license:        GPL and additional rights
parm:           mitigations:Selectively enable security mitigations for all Intel® GPUs in the system.

  auto -- enables all mitigations required for the platform [default]
  off  -- disables all mitigations

Individual mitigations can be enabled by passing a comma-separated string,
e.g. mitigations=residuals to enable only clearing residuals or
mitigations=auto,noresiduals to disable only the clear residual mitigation.
Either '!' or 'no' may be used to switch from enabling the mitigation to
disabling it.

Active mitigations for Ivybridge, Baytrail, Haswell:
  residuals -- clear all thread-local registers between contexts
parm:           lmem_bar_size:Set the lmem bar size(in MiB).
parm:           lmem_size:Set the lmem size(in MiB) for each region. (default: 0, all memory)
parm:           request_timeout_ms:Default request/fence/batch buffer expiration timeout.
parm:           enable_gvt:Enable support for Intel GVT-g graphics virtualization host support(default:false)
parm:           gsc_firmware_path:GSC firmware path to use instead of the default one
parm:           huc_firmware_path:HuC firmware path to use instead of the default one
parm:           guc_firmware_path:GuC firmware path to use instead of the default one
parm:           guc_log_level:GuC firmware logging level. Requires GuC to be loaded. (-1=auto [default], 0=disable, 1..4=enable with verbosity min..max)
parm:           enable_guc:Enable GuC load for GuC submission and/or HuC load. Required functionality can be selected using bitmask values. (-1=auto [default], 0=disable, 1=GuC submission, 2=HuC load)
parm:           mmio_debug:Enable the MMIO debug code for the first N failures (default: off). This may negatively affect performance.
parm:           memtest:Perform a read/write test of all device memory on module load (default: off)
parm:           force_probe:Force probe options for specified supported devices. See CONFIG_DRM_I915_FORCE_PROBE for details.
parm:           enable_hangcheck:Periodically check GPU activity for detecting hangs. WARNING: Disabling this can cause system wide hangs. (default: true)
parm:           error_capture:Record the GPU state following a hang. This information in /sys/class/drm/card<N>/error is vital for triaging and debugging hangs.
parm:           reset:Attempt GPU resets (0=disabled, 1=full gpu reset, 2=engine reset [default])
parm:           modeset:Deprecated. Use the 'nomodeset' kernel parameter instead.
parm:           enable_dmc_wl:Enable DMC wakelock (-1=use per-chip default, 0=disabled, 1=enabled, 2=match any register, 3=always locked) Default: -1
parm:           enable_psr2_sel_fetch:Enable PSR2 and Panel Replay selective fetch (0=disabled, 1=enabled) Default: 1
parm:           psr_safest_params:Replace PSR VBT parameters by the safest and not optimal ones. This is helpful to detect if PSR issues are related to bad values set in  VBT. (0=use VBT parameters, 1=use safest parameters)Default: 0
parm:           enable_panel_replay:Enable Panel Replay (0=disabled, 1=enabled). Default: -1 (use per-chip default)
parm:           enable_psr:Enable PSR (0=disabled, 1=enable up to PSR1, 2=enable up to PSR2) Default: -1 (use per-chip default)
parm:           enable_fbc:Enable frame buffer compression for power savings (default: -1 (use per-chip default))
parm:           enable_dp_mst:Enable multi-stream transport (MST) for new DisplayPort sinks. (default: true)
parm:           nuclear_pageflip:Force enable atomic functionality on platforms that don't have full support yet.
parm:           verbose_state_checks:Enable verbose logs (ie. WARN_ON()) in case of unexpected hw state conditions.
parm:           disable_display:Disable display (default: false)
parm:           force_reset_modeset_test:Force a modeset during gpu reset for testing (default:false). For developers only.
parm:           load_detect_test:Force-enable the VGA load detect code for testing (default:false). For developers only.
parm:           enable_dpcd_backlight:Enable support for DPCD backlight control(-1=use per-VBT LFP backlight type setting [default], 0=disabled, 1=enable, 2=force VESA interface, 3=force Intel interface)
parm:           edp_vswing:Ignore/Override vswing pre-emph table selection from VBT (0=use value from vbt [default], 1=low power swing(200mV),2=default swing(400mV))
parm:           invert_brightness:Invert backlight brightness (-1 force normal, 0 machine defaults, 1 force inversion), please report PCI device ID, subsystem vendor and subsystem device ID to dri-devel@lists.freedesktop.org, if your machine needs it. It will then be included in an upcoming module version.
parm:           enable_ips:Enable IPS (default: true)
parm:           disable_power_well:Disable display power wells when possible (-1=auto [default], 0=power wells always on, 1=power wells disabled when possible)
parm:           enable_sagv:Enable system agent voltage/frequency scaling (SAGV) (default: true)
parm:           enable_flipq:Enable DMC flip queue (default: false)
parm:           enable_dsb:Enable display state buffer (DSB) (default: true)
parm:           enable_dpt:Enable display page table (DPT) (default: true)
parm:           enable_dc:Enable power-saving display C-states. (-1=auto [default]; 0=disable; 1=up to DC5; 2=up to DC6; 3=up to DC5 with DC3CO; 4=up to DC6 with DC3CO)
parm:           vbt_sdvo_panel_type:Override/Ignore selection of SDVO panel mode in the VBT (-2=ignore, -1=auto [default], index in VBT BIOS table)
parm:           panel_use_ssc:Use Spread Spectrum Clock with panels [LVDS/eDP] (default: auto from VBT)
parm:           lvds_channel_mode:Specify LVDS channel mode (0=probe BIOS [default], 1=single-channel, 2=dual-channel)
parm:           vbt_firmware:Load VBT from specified file under /lib/firmware
parm:           dmc_firmware_path:DMC firmware path to use instead of the default one. Use /dev/null to disable DMC and runtime PM.
